5:
Allow me to introduce you. This 
handsome fellow is Aperio, 
my beloved pet.
11:
Whoa, you can summon a dragon out 
of thin air?
15:
A summoner, are you? You must be 
well-versed in the arcane arts then.
18:
So where does he come from, exactly? 
Like, another world or something?
22:
It may be an exaggeration to consider 
the contents of my grimoire to be of 
another world, but I suppose you 
could say that.
24:
Within the confines of this tome exists 
a space that houses all of my pets.
28:
I see... Its very pages fold and distort 
space itself. That is rather 
extraordinary.
31:
If you're curious, why not take a look 
inside for yourself?
39:
Of course. But only if you're willing to 
become my pet. What do you say, 
Mister Rabbit?
45:
I-I'm no rabbit! I'm the champion! S-
stay back!
48:
Champion or not, you can still 
become mine if you wish.
53:
N-no thank you! The champion is no 
one's pet!
58:
Ahaha! He always gets like this 
whenever someone calls him a rabbit.
63:
That invitation goes for you as well, 
cutie-pie.
69:
There are plenty of boys clamoring to 
become one of my playthings, you 
know?
74:
You're actually pretty cute up close... 
Although it looks like I'll need to teach 
you some manners.
79:
There's no need to be afraid... Pain is 
merely another form... of L. O. V. E.
84:
H-hey! Don't you try and use your 
feminine wiles on Alk like that!
88:
I heard some commotion. 
Is everything all right, Alk?
95:
Your face is beet-red. Are you sure 
you haven't caught a fever?
106:
Hehe. Sorry, Stella... Our conversation 
just got a little intense, that's all.
109: Let's be on our way, Aperio.
117:
My invitation's still open, by the way. 
If you ever change your mind... just 
give me the word.
118:
I'll leave an impression on you that'll 
last a lifetime.
122:
Bianca Balzaretti... I'd better keep an 
eye on her.
126: Y-yeah... That might be for the best.
129:
You really helped us out of a bind 
there, Stella. Thanks!
